summary: This is an FBI Electronic Surveillance (ELSUR) evidence envelope form documenting the transfer of intercepted communications evidence, likely related to the Epstein investigation. The form indicates it contains original magnetic tape evidence from a Title III court-authorized intercept or consensual monitoring.
keyFacts: The document is an FBI ELSUR evidence envelope form for intercepted communications.
It references a Title III court-authorized intercept or consensual monitoring.
The evidence medium is an original magnetic tape.
The form includes multiple custody signatures indicating chain of evidence handling.
The document is part of the Epstein case files (EFTA00008486).
